
Jade looked him straight in the eye, her own seeming to become an even deeper green, if that was even possible. What most enticed him about those eyes though, was the pure sense of determination they held inside. A determination that had been pushed down for months on end. But now it was back, and stronger than ever before. A smirk played with her lips, complimenting that sense of purpose flickering in her eyes. I made a good choice picking her. She has the potential to be something truly great.
She held her head high as she said her next words, ones that Ayden was sure would change the history of his life and many others from that day on.
"Yes. I will join your resistance group."